The paper proposes an online learning approach for transferring knowledge from a source robot to a target robot for trajectory tracking. This involves analyzing the similarity between the robots, characterizing the mapping to be learned, and ensuring stability of the overall system. These topics are all related to robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG), with elements of control systems (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV) also present.
